51
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:55,300
I thought you were
tougher than that.

52
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:59,266
[laughing]

53
00:04:59,366 --> 00:05:00,766
[laughing]

54
00:05:05,133 --> 00:05:07,933
-I can't believe these two are
sleeping the afternoon away--

55
00:05:08,033 --> 00:05:12,800
such a shame, especially
on such a beautiful day.

56
00:05:15,966 --> 00:05:17,600
Well, it is a little cloudy.

57
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:19,533
[yawning]

58
00:05:19,633 --> 00:05:20,966
[boiling]

59
00:05:22,966 --> 00:05:24,800
RANMA: Whoa.

60
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,900
Does that ever look good.

61
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,033
-Eat as much as you like, Ranma.

62
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:32,500
-This is excellent, Akane.

63
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,000
You're the best
cook in the world.

64
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:37,133
-Oh, well, it was nothing.

65
00:05:37,233 --> 00:05:40,766
-A wicked cook,
smart-- what a girl.

66
00:05:40,866 --> 00:05:41,307
-Ranma.

67
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:45,900
[giggling] You stay here.

68
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:46,900
I'll make you some more.

69
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:57,000
What's happening?

70
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:59,100
HAPPOSAI: Hey, get out my dream.

71
00:05:59,200 --> 00:05:59,641
-Huh?

72
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:04,733
[laughing]

73
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:06,500
-You'll never beat me, old man.

74
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,041
Never.

75
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:14,500
-Don't you know
this is my dream?

76
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,041
-No!

77
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:15,541
No!

78
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,082
No!

79
00:06:30,866 --> 00:06:31,300
-Huh?

80
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,066
Akane?

81
00:06:32,166 --> 00:06:33,633
-Ranma?

82
00:06:33,733 --> 00:06:35,366
So where-- where are we?

83
00:06:35,466 --> 00:06:36,833
HAPPOSAI: You're in my dream.

84
00:06:36,933 --> 00:06:37,374
-Huh?

85
00:06:42,900 --> 00:06:46,233
-So how did we end up in your
stupid dream anyhow, you freak?

86
00:06:46,333 --> 00:06:47,200
-Yeah, how?

87
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:49,133
I'd rather be in my own dream.

88
00:06:49,233 --> 00:06:51,766
-Cause I was the
first to fall asleep.

89
00:06:51,866 --> 00:06:53,900
I thought you'd figure
that one out for yourself.

90
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:54,866
-You--

91
00:06:54,966 --> 00:06:56,300
[laughing]

92
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:07,066
-Pathetic excuse
for a leprechaun.

93
00:07:07,166 --> 00:07:09,533
-I'd say this is no
different than real life.

94
00:07:09,633 --> 00:07:11,033
[laughing]

95
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,166
-One at a time, girls.

96
00:07:17,266 --> 00:07:21,066
Oh, and remember to put your
phone numbers neatly this time.

97
00:07:21,166 --> 00:07:22,466
-I take that back.

98
00:07:22,566 --> 00:07:23,766
This could only be his dream.

99
00:07:23,866 --> 00:07:25,166
[laughing]

100
00:07:34,733 --> 00:07:36,066
[laughing]

101
00:07:39,366 --> 00:07:42,100
-Whoa, this place is so tacky.

102
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:42,900
-I know.

103
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,900
Huh?

104
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:48,033
Hey, these are mine.

105
00:07:48,133 --> 00:07:49,433
[laughing]

106
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:53,866
-And so are all
these other pairs.

107
00:07:53,966 --> 00:07:54,800
-That's right.

108
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:56,033
Why, you'll find
every single pair

109
00:07:56,133 --> 00:07:58,600
you've ever worn,
including a few diapers.

110
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:03,166
Don't forget this is my
dream, sweetie. [laughing]

111
00:08:03,266 --> 00:08:06,100
-Why would you do that, huh?

112
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:08,633
-I tell ya, everybody
needs a hobby.

113
00:08:08,733 --> 00:08:10,033
And this one's mine.

114
00:08:10,133 --> 00:08:10,574
-Gross!

115
00:08:13,833 --> 00:08:16,900
-Oh, Ranma, look what
I've got for you.

116
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,933
-You-- you're disgusting!

117
00:08:19,033 --> 00:08:20,733
-Hey, you put this on, or else--

118
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:23,733
AKANE: Hey, Ranma.

119
00:08:23,833 --> 00:08:25,300
Now you can fight
him like a man.

120
00:08:28,133 --> 00:08:29,966
-Hey, what gives?

121
00:08:30,066 --> 00:08:31,933
I'm still a girl.

122
00:08:32,033 --> 00:08:33,000
[laughing]

123
00:08:34,133 --> 00:08:35,266
-How many times do
I have to tell you?

124
00:08:35,366 --> 00:08:36,900
This is my dream.

125
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,366
And in my sick and twisted
little imagination,

126
00:08:39,466 --> 00:08:40,300
I call the shots.

127
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:42,933
So if I want Ranma
to stay a girl--

128
00:08:43,033 --> 00:08:43,833
-Hurry, Ranma!

129
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:49,633
-Remember, you can
run, but I'll find you.

130
00:08:49,733 --> 00:08:52,000
[panting]

131
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:53,433
-Come on, Akane.

132
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:55,866
We have to find a way
out of this dream.

133
00:08:55,966 --> 00:08:57,633
-Yeah, cause I don't
want to find out

134
00:08:57,733 --> 00:08:58,833
what happens if we stay.

135
00:08:58,933 --> 00:08:59,833
RANMA: What do you mean?

136
00:08:59,933 --> 00:09:00,633
-Cause he's crazy.

137
00:09:00,733 --> 00:09:02,233
-OK, I'll give you that.

138
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:03,433
But where are you headed to?

139
00:09:06,433 --> 00:09:09,300
-I have absolutely no idea.

140
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:11,200
-Why, you-- I
should've known you

141
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:12,833
didn't have any kind of plan.

142
00:09:12,933 --> 00:09:13,600
-Oh, yeah?

143
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:14,800
Then let's hear your plan.

144
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:16,900
-Hey, I was following you.

145
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,166
[grunting]

146
00:09:19,266 --> 00:09:20,666
[sighing]

147
00:09:21,933 --> 00:09:24,633
-OK, we just got to
think this thing through.

148
00:09:24,733 --> 00:09:27,300
-I agree.

149
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,200
Akane, look!

150
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:28,741
-Huh?

151
00:09:31,566 --> 00:09:34,800
-Hey, how did Nabiki's dream
end up inside this one?

152
00:09:38,766 --> 00:09:39,833
[sighing]

153
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:45,133
-Her dream's bound to be
better than the freak's.

154
00:09:49,033 --> 00:09:50,500
AKANE: It sure is dark in here.

155
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:51,866
RANMA: Yeah.

156
00:09:51,966 --> 00:09:54,633
AKANE: And it doesn't look
like there's much here.

157
00:09:54,733 --> 00:09:56,200
[inaudible]

158
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:56,833
[gasping]

159
00:09:56,933 --> 00:09:58,400
-Hey, what's that?

160
00:09:58,500 --> 00:09:59,966
-You think we
should check it out?

161
00:10:00,066 --> 00:10:00,633
-Let's go!

162
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:05,933
What's this?

163
00:10:06,033 --> 00:10:06,900
-Ranma, look.

164
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,100
-Hm?

165
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:10,966
-Hey, you think this could
be a way out of here?

166
00:10:11,066 --> 00:10:12,866
-Oh.

167
00:10:12,966 --> 00:10:13,407
Hm.

168
00:10:13,466 --> 00:10:13,948
[beeping]

169
00:10:13,966 --> 00:10:15,233
[gasping]

170
00:10:16,366 --> 00:10:18,700
-To proceed, please
insert 1,000 yen.

171
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:21,533
To proceed, please
insert 1,000 yen.

172
00:10:21,633 --> 00:10:22,966
RANMA: Insert this!

173
00:10:23,066 --> 00:10:25,033
Paid in full.

174
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:29,133
Oh, Ranma, that area's
off limits unless you pay.

175
00:10:29,233 --> 00:10:30,400
-Nabiki.

176
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:33,233
-There's no way I'm
paying you a single yen.

177
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:35,166
-OK, that's fine with me.

178
00:10:35,266 --> 00:10:37,533
But in my dream
it's pay-as-you-go.

179
00:10:37,633 --> 00:10:39,100
-So how much is it?

180
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:41,566
You name your price,
and I'll pay it.

181
00:10:41,666 --> 00:10:42,666
-3,000 yen.

182
00:10:42,766 --> 00:10:43,207
-What?

183
00:10:43,266 --> 00:10:44,366
3,000 yen?

184
00:10:44,466 --> 00:10:45,933
-That's just to open the gate.

185
00:10:46,033 --> 00:10:48,200
Another 3,000 to point
out the right one.

186
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,566
-Well, thank you.

187
00:10:52,666 --> 00:10:53,700
-Well?

188
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,566
-You'll find the gate
right over there, Akane.

189
00:10:58,966 --> 00:11:00,233
-Well, see you later, Nabiki.

190
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:07,082
-Look!

191
00:11:10,033 --> 00:11:10,474
-Huh?

192
00:11:10,533 --> 00:11:11,600
[laughing]

193
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:15,433
-Welcome to my nightmare.

194
00:11:15,533 --> 00:11:16,866
-She tricked us.

195
00:11:16,966 --> 00:11:20,466
-Well, well, it's not very
nice to talk about someone

196
00:11:20,566 --> 00:11:22,000
behind their back.

197
00:11:22,100 --> 00:11:23,933
-N--Nabiki?

198
00:11:24,033 --> 00:11:27,466
-Now you must ask
Master Happosai.

199
00:11:27,566 --> 00:11:30,900
-Nabiki, can you rub my back?

200
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:33,100
-Coming, hun.

201
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:35,633
-I think I'm going to be sick.

202
00:11:35,733 --> 00:11:36,800
-Isn't this great?

203
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:39,166
I have never been this
happy until I decided

204
00:11:39,266 --> 00:11:41,866
to move into Happosai's
little fantasy world.

205
00:11:56,202 --> 00:11:57,335
-Open wide, my sweet.

206
00:11:57,435 --> 00:11:59,002
-Ahh.

207
00:12:01,835 --> 00:12:05,168
-Oh, please, Nabiki,
would you stop it already?

208
00:12:05,268 --> 00:12:07,002
-You'll figure it
out for yourself.

209
00:12:07,102 --> 00:12:09,368
There's no point in
fighting him in his dream.

210
00:12:09,468 --> 00:12:12,168
-You know that Nabiki's
smarter than she looks.

211
00:12:12,268 --> 00:12:13,468
Huh?

212
00:12:13,568 --> 00:12:15,335
-By the way, you still
owe me for dinner.

213
00:12:15,435 --> 00:12:17,335
-Maybe a bit too smart.

214
00:12:17,435 --> 00:12:18,335
-Oh, boy.

215
00:12:18,435 --> 00:12:18,876
-Ranma.

216
00:12:18,935 --> 00:12:20,202
-Huh?

217
00:12:20,302 --> 00:12:21,602
[whispering]

218
00:12:22,602 --> 00:12:23,868
-There's no way.

219
00:12:23,968 --> 00:12:25,802
Do it yourself, Akane.

220
00:12:25,902 --> 00:12:27,802
-You want to stay here forever?

221
00:12:27,902 --> 00:12:29,702
Let's just hope you
like modelling underwear

222
00:12:29,802 --> 00:12:30,902
for him, Ranma.

223
00:12:31,002 --> 00:12:32,102
-[grunting]

224
00:12:36,368 --> 00:12:37,102
NABIKI: Here you go.

225
00:12:37,202 --> 00:12:38,068
HAPPOSAI: Oh, ho.

226
00:12:38,168 --> 00:12:39,602
Oh, why thank you.

227
00:12:39,702 --> 00:12:42,435
[slurping]

228
00:12:42,535 --> 00:12:45,268
-Yoo-hoo.

229
00:12:45,368 --> 00:12:49,335
Maybe we can come to
some kind of arrangement.

230
00:12:49,435 --> 00:12:51,102
That is if you're
willing to wake up

231
00:12:51,202 --> 00:12:52,968
from this little fantasy.

232
00:12:53,068 --> 00:12:55,168
-Name it.

233
00:12:55,268 --> 00:12:56,068
-Well?

234
00:12:56,168 --> 00:12:56,735
GROUP: Happosai!

235
00:12:59,968 --> 00:13:02,735
-No, I'm staying right here.

236
00:13:02,835 --> 00:13:05,635
-Why that little-- ah!

237
00:13:05,735 --> 00:13:07,068
[laughing]

238
00:13:07,168 --> 00:13:08,535
[interposing voices]

239
00:13:13,535 --> 00:13:15,902
-Nabiki's our only
hope out of here.

240
00:13:16,002 --> 00:13:16,768
-3,000 yen.

241
00:13:16,868 --> 00:13:17,335
-Huh?

242
00:13:17,435 --> 00:13:18,568
But what for?

243
00:13:18,668 --> 00:13:20,735
-You want information, you pay.

244
00:13:20,835 --> 00:13:24,102
-But that's all I've got.

245
00:13:24,202 --> 00:13:26,035
-Thank you.

246
00:13:26,135 --> 00:13:28,668
You know, I'm making some
pretty good cash in here.

247
00:13:28,768 --> 00:13:29,835
-OK, I paid.

248
00:13:29,935 --> 00:13:34,068
Now tell us how to
get out of here.

249
00:13:34,168 --> 00:13:36,068
-I don't know.

250
00:13:36,168 --> 00:13:38,035
-What'd you do that for?

251
00:13:38,135 --> 00:13:39,435
-Please, Ranma.

252
00:13:39,535 --> 00:13:42,668
I'm just as weirded out in this
pointless fantasy as you are.

253
00:13:42,768 --> 00:13:46,102
-Well, you sure seem
to be enjoying it.

254
00:13:46,202 --> 00:13:50,202
-Give me back my money, Nabiki.

255
00:13:50,302 --> 00:13:52,368
-But Akane, you only
paid me with dream money.

256
00:13:52,468 --> 00:13:53,502
[growling]

257
00:13:54,402 --> 00:13:56,568
-OK, OK, OK, I'll tell you.

258
00:13:56,668 --> 00:13:59,502
Just promise you're not
gonna hurt me, all right?

259
00:13:59,602 --> 00:14:00,568
-OK.

260
00:14:00,668 --> 00:14:02,068
[laughing]

261
00:14:06,402 --> 00:14:06,843
-What?

262
00:14:06,902 --> 00:14:07,935
Fainting?

263
00:14:08,035 --> 00:14:10,202
-Yeah, if you can get
him to faint somehow,

264
00:14:10,302 --> 00:14:11,435
then he'll snap out of it.

265
00:14:11,535 --> 00:14:13,902
-Oh, man, this is gonna be easy.

266
00:14:14,002 --> 00:14:16,868
-Don't be so sure.

267
00:14:16,968 --> 00:14:18,268
[moaning]

268
00:14:19,768 --> 00:14:22,802
GROUP: Oh, you're so big
and strong, Happosai.

269
00:14:26,635 --> 00:14:27,935
-Ahh!

270
00:14:28,035 --> 00:14:29,368
Ahh!

271
00:14:29,468 --> 00:14:30,968
Ahh!

272
00:14:31,068 --> 00:14:32,402
Ahh!

273
00:14:32,502 --> 00:14:36,768
[screaming] My back.

274
00:14:36,868 --> 00:14:37,835
[laughing]

275
00:14:38,768 --> 00:14:40,168
-I love it when they play rough.

276
00:14:40,268 --> 00:14:43,368
[laughing]

277
00:14:43,468 --> 00:14:44,635
-That should take care of him.

278
00:14:54,202 --> 00:14:56,102
GROUP: Oh.

279
00:14:56,202 --> 00:14:56,643
Happosai!

280
00:15:00,735 --> 00:15:01,668
[gasping]

281
00:15:02,835 --> 00:15:04,568
-Should've used a
be bigger mallet.

282
00:15:04,668 --> 00:15:06,068
[laughing]

283
00:15:07,668 --> 00:15:09,568
-I'm back.

284
00:15:09,668 --> 00:15:12,035
There's one thing I should
tell you about my dream.

285
00:15:12,135 --> 00:15:14,402
It's impossible to wake me.

286
00:15:14,502 --> 00:15:16,335
[laughing]

287
00:15:16,435 --> 00:15:18,168
-Check.

288
00:15:18,268 --> 00:15:19,535
And it looks like
there's nothing

289
00:15:19,635 --> 00:15:21,268
you can do about it, my friend.

290
00:15:21,368 --> 00:15:23,268
[laughing]

291
00:15:23,368 --> 00:15:24,568
[snoring]

292
00:15:26,802 --> 00:15:31,502
-Saotome, I said check.

293
00:15:31,602 --> 00:15:34,768
[yawning]

294
00:15:34,868 --> 00:15:36,102
[boiling]

295
00:15:36,702 --> 00:15:37,568
-Hm?

296
00:15:37,668 --> 00:15:39,068
[laughing]

297
00:15:40,168 --> 00:15:41,402
-Look who's here.

298
00:15:41,502 --> 00:15:42,302
-What happened?

299
00:15:42,402 --> 00:15:43,835
-How did we get here?

300
00:15:43,935 --> 00:15:45,502
-You're in my dream.

301
00:15:45,602 --> 00:15:49,035
-We're in his dream?

302
00:15:49,135 --> 00:15:50,135
GENMA AND SOUN: Excuse us.

303
00:15:54,368 --> 00:15:56,568
-That really hurt.

304
00:15:56,668 --> 00:15:58,068
-It sure did.

305
00:15:58,168 --> 00:15:59,502
[laughing]

306
00:15:59,602 --> 00:16:02,435
-It's like I said,
you're in my dream.

307
00:16:02,535 --> 00:16:04,968
And everything I
dream comes true.

308
00:16:05,068 --> 00:16:06,168
GENMA AND SOUN: Huh?

309
00:16:06,268 --> 00:16:09,368
-M--M-- M-- Master are you
sure you're comfortable?

310
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:11,768
GENMA AND SOUN: How about
a quick massage, Master?

311
00:16:11,868 --> 00:16:13,935
-Oh, knock it off.

312
00:16:14,035 --> 00:16:15,202
Huh?

313
00:16:15,302 --> 00:16:15,743
What?

314
00:16:19,202 --> 00:16:20,535
[snoring]

315
00:16:30,735 --> 00:16:33,735
-Wake up you perverted
little twerp.

316
00:16:41,135 --> 00:16:43,935
-Ah, that was close.

317
00:16:44,035 --> 00:16:46,635
-I thought you were going
back to wake him up, Ranma.

318
00:16:46,735 --> 00:16:50,002
-Hey, would you get off my case.

319
00:16:50,102 --> 00:16:50,935
-Oh!

320
00:16:51,035 --> 00:16:51,968
And I thought I
could count on you

321
00:16:52,068 --> 00:16:53,468
to get us out of this nightmare.

322
00:16:53,568 --> 00:16:54,268
-Huh?

323
00:16:54,368 --> 00:16:56,968
Akane, look!

324
00:16:57,068 --> 00:16:57,509
-Huh?

325
00:17:00,735 --> 00:17:06,602
I think it goes this
way. [laughing] Huh?

326
00:17:06,702 --> 00:17:07,602
Oh, well.

327
00:17:07,702 --> 00:17:09,902
That's enough
excitement for one day.

328
00:17:10,002 --> 00:17:11,302
[boiling]

329
00:17:12,368 --> 00:17:14,635
-Nice to have you back, Genma.

330
00:17:14,735 --> 00:17:15,768
-Oh!

331
00:17:15,868 --> 00:17:18,602
We were all counting on
you to wake him up, pop

332
00:17:18,702 --> 00:17:20,235
-Don't worry about it, Ranma.

333
00:17:20,335 --> 00:17:21,635
I know what I'm doing.

334
00:17:21,735 --> 00:17:24,435
[laughing] Huh?

335
00:17:24,535 --> 00:17:25,735
-Oh, man.

336
00:17:25,835 --> 00:17:27,902
I gotta figure out a way
to get that little munchkin

337
00:17:28,002 --> 00:17:29,135
to pass out.

338
00:17:29,235 --> 00:17:30,702
-You don't get it, do you?

339
00:17:30,802 --> 00:17:31,568
There is another way.

340
00:17:31,668 --> 00:17:32,502
-Huh?

341
00:17:32,602 --> 00:17:33,902
Oh, great, Nabiki,
let's hear it.

342
00:17:34,002 --> 00:17:35,802
-1,000 yen.

343
00:17:35,902 --> 00:17:36,835
-500.

344
00:17:36,935 --> 00:17:40,035
-OK, you got a deal.

345
00:17:40,135 --> 00:17:41,402
-Tell us!

346
00:17:41,502 --> 00:17:46,402
-Happosai isn't necessarily
the only one that has to faint.

347
00:17:46,502 --> 00:17:47,868
-Now I get it.

348
00:17:47,968 --> 00:17:50,235
-Yeah, so do I.

349
00:17:50,335 --> 00:17:51,702
[screaming]

350
00:17:52,502 --> 00:17:53,802
-Would you stand still?

351
00:17:53,902 --> 00:17:56,135
Don't you remember
what Nabiki just said?

352
00:17:56,235 --> 00:17:57,968
It doesn't have to be Happosai.

353
00:17:58,068 --> 00:17:59,568
-Get real.

354
00:17:59,668 --> 00:18:01,968
-You are such a wimp, Ranma.

355
00:18:02,068 --> 00:18:04,735
-Psst, Akane, if you
faint in this dream,

356
00:18:04,835 --> 00:18:06,802
then will you wake up too?

357
00:18:06,902 --> 00:18:08,535
-Huh?

358
00:18:08,635 --> 00:18:11,502
-But the Master says he
doesn't want to wake up.

359
00:18:11,602 --> 00:18:12,468
-Please.

360
00:18:12,568 --> 00:18:13,668
That's because he's
having the time

361
00:18:13,768 --> 00:18:16,035
of his life with those girls.

362
00:18:16,135 --> 00:18:16,968
-What now?

363
00:18:17,068 --> 00:18:18,268
-We must--

364
00:18:18,368 --> 00:18:20,568
GENMA AND SOUN: Give him an
old-fashioned wake-up call.

365
00:18:21,402 --> 00:18:21,843
-Huh?

366
00:18:24,802 --> 00:18:28,335
-If this doesn't wake him
up, I don't know what will.

367
00:18:28,435 --> 00:18:30,202
-Look, Saotome, I
think the Master's

368
00:18:30,302 --> 00:18:32,668
starting to snap out of it.

369
00:18:32,768 --> 00:18:34,668
Hey, I'm starting to enjoy this.

370
00:18:34,768 --> 00:18:38,102
-And it's good exercise too.

371
00:18:38,202 --> 00:18:40,535
-[inaudible].

372
00:18:40,635 --> 00:18:41,568
-Hey!

373
00:18:41,668 --> 00:18:44,935
Would you two quit
hogging all the fun?

374
00:18:45,035 --> 00:18:46,968
-I got ya.

375
00:18:47,068 --> 00:18:47,509
-Saotome!

376
00:18:52,502 --> 00:18:54,235
-Hey, stop!

377
00:18:54,335 --> 00:18:56,802
Time to fight back.

378
00:18:56,902 --> 00:18:58,302
-All right.

379
00:18:58,402 --> 00:19:00,002
-He's gonna make us faint.

380
00:19:00,102 --> 00:19:01,002
-It's working.

381
00:19:12,968 --> 00:19:14,368
[moaning]

382
00:19:18,402 --> 00:19:19,802
-Huh?

383
00:19:19,902 --> 00:19:21,768
GENMA AND SOUN: Huh?

384
00:19:21,868 --> 00:19:23,268
-What the--

385
00:19:23,368 --> 00:19:24,735
-You fools!

386
00:19:24,835 --> 00:19:26,968
How many times do
I have to tell you?

387
00:19:27,068 --> 00:19:29,168
You can't escape my dream.

388
00:19:29,268 --> 00:19:32,368
Even if you or I faint, it
doesn't make any difference,

389
00:19:32,468 --> 00:19:35,035
because you're trapped
in here for eternity.

390
00:19:35,135 --> 00:19:36,402
[gasping]

391
00:19:40,435 --> 00:19:41,835
[moaning]

392
00:19:46,868 --> 00:19:48,768
-Ranma!

393
00:19:48,868 --> 00:19:52,068
-Well, I suppose that's
pretty much the end of Ranma.

394
00:19:52,168 --> 00:19:52,635
-You mean--

395
00:19:52,735 --> 00:19:53,835
-I'm kidding.

396
00:19:53,935 --> 00:19:55,835
Nobody's going to bite
the big one in this dream.

397
00:19:55,935 --> 00:19:57,302
-You sure?

398
00:19:57,402 --> 00:19:58,635
[moaning]

399
00:19:59,968 --> 00:20:00,435
ALL: Huh?

400
00:20:00,535 --> 00:20:00,976
Huh?

401
00:20:03,535 --> 00:20:05,602
-On the downside, this
could go on forever.

402
00:20:10,868 --> 00:20:11,309
ALL: Huh?

403
00:20:11,368 --> 00:20:11,809
-Hm?

404
00:20:18,302 --> 00:20:19,202
-What's happening?

405
00:20:31,168 --> 00:20:33,335
-Hey, everyone.

406
00:20:33,435 --> 00:20:34,002
Lunch is ready.

407
00:20:45,535 --> 00:20:46,502
[snoring]

408
00:20:49,302 --> 00:20:51,435
-Huh?

409
00:20:51,535 --> 00:20:54,635
I just had the best dream ever.

410
00:20:54,735 --> 00:20:59,268
But it's such a shame that
I had to wake up from it.

411
00:20:59,368 --> 00:21:02,368
-I'm glad to hear it.

412
00:21:02,468 --> 00:21:05,668
-So you gonna tell us all
about it, you old goat?

413
00:21:05,768 --> 00:21:06,902
-Huh?

414
00:21:07,002 --> 00:21:09,435
-There's no way it was
as good as my dream.

415
00:21:09,535 --> 00:21:11,735
-Don't be so sure
about that, Nabiki.

416
00:21:11,835 --> 00:21:12,835
-Yeah.

417
00:21:12,935 --> 00:21:14,235
GENMA AND SOUN: Please
forgive us, Master.

418
00:21:14,335 --> 00:21:15,002
-Huh?

419
00:21:15,102 --> 00:21:17,102
I just had a little dream.

420
00:21:17,202 --> 00:21:18,735
Is that so wrong?

421
00:21:18,835 --> 00:21:22,435
ALL: We know about your dream.

422
00:21:22,535 --> 00:21:23,435
Take that!

423
00:21:28,002 --> 00:21:30,868
-Please hurry back, or
your lunch will get cold.

424
00:21:30,968 --> 00:21:31,409
-OK.

425
00:21:44,363 --> 00:21:47,763
[theme music]

426
00:23:17,139 --> 00:23:20,272
AKANE (VOICEOVER): Well, if
Nabiki wants him so much,

427
00:23:20,372 --> 00:23:24,039
then fine then, she
can be Ranma's fiance.

428
00:23:24,139 --> 00:23:28,806
Next time on "Ranma 1/2",
Nabiki, Ranma's new fiance.

429
00:23:28,906 --> 00:23:30,206
We'll see you there.

